# Quibi Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Context
Quibi is an anonymous employee feedback platform built with Next.js 16 (App Router), Tailwind CSS v4, and shadcn/ui.

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Define shared types in `types/index.ts`
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use explicit return types for functions

### React & Next.js
- Use Server Components by default
- Add "use client" directive only when needed (hooks, event handlers, browser APIs)
- Use the App Router conventions (app/ directory)
- Async components for data fetching

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS classes
- Use `cn()` from `lib/utils` for conditional classes
- Primary color is indigo/violet (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`)
- Use semantic design tokens from globals.css

### Components
- Reuse components from `components/ui/` (shadcn/ui)
- Create feature components in `components/[feature]/`
- Layout components are in `components/layout/`

## File Organization
```
app/           - Pages and API routes
components/    - React components
  layout/      - Navbar, Footer, etc.
  ui/          - shadcn/ui components (don't modify)
  [feature]/   - Feature-specific components
hooks/         - Custom React hooks
lib/           - Utilities and helpers
types/         - TypeScript interfaces
```

## Key Patterns

### Data Fetching
- Prefer Server Components for data fetching
- Use SWR for client-side data that needs real-time updates
- Never fetch inside useEffect

### Forms
- Use shadcn/ui form components (Input, Textarea, Button)
- Add proper validation
- Show loading states during submission

### Navigation
- Update `components/layout/Navbar.tsx` when adding new pages
- Use Next.js Link component for internal navigation

